cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses gradient-based meta-learning techniques for few-shot learning and fast adaptation problems, which are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper specifically focuses on addressing practical difficulties when operating on high-dimensional parameter spaces in extreme low-data regimes, which is a common challenge in machine learning and computer vision research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.NE.
